This was a bug we had seen multiple times on Hadoop 2.6.2. And the following analysis is based on the core dump, logs, and code in 2017 with Hadoop 2.6.2. We hadn't seen it after 2.9 in our env. However, it was because of the RPC retry policy change and other changes. There's still a possibility even with the current code if I didn't miss anything.
High-level description:
 We had seen a starving mapper issue several times. The MR job stuck in a live lock state and couldn't make any progress. The queue is full so the pending mapper canâ€™t get any resource to continue, and the application master failed to preempt the reducer, thus causing the job to be stuck. The reason why the application master didnâ€™t preempt the reducer was that there was a leaked container in assigned mappers. The node manager failed to report the completed container to the resource manager.
